100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 16, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and international cooperation amidst rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to spark public protests, as citizens increasingly questioned the law's effectiveness. In China, clashes between warlords and nationalist forces intensified, threatening stability in the region. Meanwhile, the British Parliament faced mounting pressure over economic challenges, including unemployment and labor unrest.
